HEADWORD: Staminate
<hw>Stam"i*nate</hw> <pr>(-n⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>staminatus</ets> consisting of threads, fr. <ets>stamen</ets>
thread: cf. F. <ets>stamin⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Furnished with stamens; producing stamens.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having stamens, but lacking pistils.</def>⟦br⟧
